ops.insert: why do countries try to protect their own firms from exposure to the world market

textDelta: why do countries try to protect their own firms from exposure to the world markets? There are a few reasons why countries might try to protect their firms from exposure to the world markets. One reason is that the country may want to keep its firms' profits and resources within its borders in order to benefit from them itself. Additionally, a country may be concerned that its firms will be unable to compete with foreign firms if they are exposed to global competition. By shielding its firms from the world markets, the country can give them a competitive edge.
